<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>

<p>A single block of <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> <seg cert="low"><rs type="objectType">Architrave</rs> block</seg> (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">2.59</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.39</measure> x depth not measurable).</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p>l. 1, <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.07</measure>, l.2, <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.06-0.065</measure></p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p>
<date exact="none" notAfter="-1" notBefore="-33">Late first century B.C.</date> (<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>)</p>
</div>
<div type="edition" lang="grc">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>
 
<ab><lb n="1"/><persName type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Μένανδρος">Μένανδρος</name>  <persName type="aphrodisian"><name reg="Ἄτταλος">Ἀττάλου</name></persName></persName>  <supplied reason="lost"><w lemma="ὁ">τὰ</w>  <w lemma="ἐπιστύλιον">ἐπιστύλια</w></supplied><lb n="2"/> <w lemma="καί">καὶ</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τὸν</w> <w>ἐπ′</w> <w lemma="αὐτός">αὐτῶν</w> <supplied reason="lost"><w lemma="κόσμος">κόσμον</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τῶι</w> <w lemma="δῆμος">Δήμωι</w></supplied>    </ab>
</div>


<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>Menandros son of Attalos, <supplied reason="lost">the epistyles</supplied> and the <supplied reason="lost">decoration</supplied> on them <supplied reason="lost">for the People</supplied>.</p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>This is one of a group of such texts, all others found re-used near the South-east Gate, dedicating an <term>epistylion</term>, with its decoration (<term>kosmos</term>) to the Demos: <xref type="inscription" n="1126" href="120405">12.405</xref> (=CIG 2752), <xref type="inscription" n="1103" href="120503">12.503</xref> (=LBW 1589), <xref type="inscription" n="1104" href="120504">12.504</xref> (= LBW 1591), <xref type="inscription" n="1127" href="120505">12.505</xref> (=MAMA 439), <xref type="inscription" n="1128" href="120506">12.506</xref> (=MAMA 440), <xref type="inscription" n="1129" href="130503">13.503</xref> (=MAMA 441), <xref type="inscription" n="1130" href="120406">12.406</xref> (=MAMA 442), <xref type="inscription" n="1131" href="120407">12.407</xref> (=MAMA 443), <xref type="inscription" n="1132" href="120408">12.408</xref> (=MAMA 442), <xref type="inscription" n="1133" href="120404">12.404</xref> (= Reinach 127 and 128).</p>
<p>The group discussed by<bibl n="jmr1990"><author>Reynolds</author>, 'Inscriptions and the Building of the Temple', <title>Aphrodisias Papers </title>(Ann Arbor, 1990), 37-40, 39.</bibl>.</p></div><div type="history" n="locations">
<head>Locations</head>
<p><rs type="found"><rs type="monuList">Necropolis, South-west</rs>: In a reservoir 3 km. west of the city wall (the Theatre bears 75o); same general area as <xref type="inscription" n="546" href="130609">13.609</xref> (=MAMA 411), <xref type="inscription" n="379" href="130502">13.502</xref> (=MAMA 533).</rs><rs type="origLocation">Unknown</rs><rs type="lastLocation">Findspot (1934)</rs>
</p>
</div>
